=== HOARD VALUATION ===

Total estimated value of a hoard is the sum of all contained item values.

Cursed items must be flagged separately in valuation reports -- their
market value is considered zero for insurance purposes.

Magical items are valued at 3x their base estimated value.


=== THREAT ASSESSMENT ===

A hero who has successfully stolen items (partial_theft or full_theft
outcome) is automatically escalated one threat level.

A hero confirmed deceased (isDeceased = true) is downgraded to negligible
threat.

A hero of class 'legendary' cannot be downgraded below 'high'.

More than two incursions by the same hero triggers a mandatory lair
security review.


=== ACQUISITION RULES ===

Items acquired via tribute are exempt from the standard 10% registry tax.

Items acquired via theft_from_hero must have an associated incursion record.

Inheritance acquisitions require a certified Death Certificate of the
previous hoard owner.


=== LAIR OPERATIONS ===

A lair marked inactive cannot receive new hoard items.

A dragon may not have more than one active primary lair at a time.

Lairs of type sea_trench require a waterproofing surcharge on all stored
spellbooks.
